  "texts": [
    "For broader Eating Disorders, 6 studies leverage datasets between 10K and 100K, while 3 others operate with datasets in the 100K to 1 million range.",
    "Finally, research on Mental Disorders encompasses datasets varying from 1K to more than 1 million data points.",
    "The distribution of the primary focus of these studies is illustrated in Figure 7 (InputRQ4) The majority of the studies (n=29) we collected focused on anorexia, while 12 studies conducted a broader investigation of EDs in general rather than focusing on a specific type.",
    "Additionally, three studies had a more extensive scope, delving into various mental disorders, including but not limited to EDs, while one study focused on binge eating.",
    "Table 3 summarizes all the papers that we identified following our strategy, including the ones from eRisk."
  ]
}